d":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box#alignment","content":"Alignment"},"1335":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-10","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box#rtl-support","content":"RTL Support"},"1336":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-11","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box#design-tokens","content":"Design Tokens"},"1337":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-12","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box","content":"Box is a polymorphic layout component that renders as any HTML element or custom component via the `as` prop. It provides consistent spacing, elevation, rounding, and self-alignment within flex or grid containers."},"1338":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-13","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box","content":"**Important**: Since `Flex` and `Grid` extend `Box`, prefer them for layouts. Use `Box` only when you need a non-flex, non-grid container."},"1339":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-14","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#props","content":"The `Box` component accepts the following props:"},"1340":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-15","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#scale-sizes","content":"The spacing props use semantic t-shirt sizes for padding, gap, and other spacing properties:"},"1341":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-16","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#scale-sizes","content":"`xs` - Extra small spacing"},"1342":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-17","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#sca